The traditional accentual system oi the Romans did not resemble that oi the Greeks in all particulars. The word ommim is merely a translation oi the Greek προσῳδία, and the names oi the accents are also the same. Still, from a study oi this passage, important differences may be noted.

Arate. This may stand on any one oi the last three syllables in Greek; in Latin it can stand only on the penult or the antepenult, never on the ultimo. In both languages it may stand on short or on long syllables.
